<item>
            <title>[PIG-1635] Logical simplifier does not simplify away constants under AND and OR; after simplificaion the ordering of operands of AND and OR may get changed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1635</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;b = FILTER a by (( f1 &amp;gt; 1) AND (1 == 1))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b = FILTER a by ((f1 &amp;gt; 1) OR ( 1==0))&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;should be simplified to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b = FILTER a by f1 &amp;gt; 1;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regarding ordering change, an example is that &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b = filter a by ((f1 is not null) AND (f2 is not null));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even without possible simplification, the expression is changed to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b = filter a by ((f2 is not null) AND (f1 is not null));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even though the ordering change in this case, and probably in most other cases, does not create any difference, but for two reasons some users might care about the ordering: if stateful UDFs are used as operands of AND or OR; and if the ordering is intended by the application designer to maximize the chances to shortcut the composite boolean evaluation. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
